{"type":"message","id":"6ace9c6d","parentId":"55894197","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:25:36.064Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 16:25 GMT+2] SKILLS FLEET AUDIT & PROOF OF LIFE.\n\n1.  **Skills Audit (40 Skills):**\n    *   Scan `docs_archive/KNOWLEDGE_BASE.md`.\n    *   Compare against `openclaw.json` (active skills) and `skills/` directory.\n    *   *Categorize:* Installed (Active) vs Planned (Knowledge only).\n\n2.  **Top-5 Deep Dive (Evidence):**\n    *   *orjson:* Read `src/dmarket/api/client.py` (lines 1-20). Confirm `import ... as json`.\n    *   *grep-master:* Demonstrate `Select-String` usage in *this* task logic (Self-Proof).\n    *   *Ed25519:* Read `tests/integration_sandbox.py` output or file content.\n    *   *Fleet:* Read `src/bot_730.pid`, `src/bot_570.pid`, etc.\n\n3.  **GIL Analysis (Subinterpreter vs Multiprocessing):**\n    *   *Research:* Can `subinterpreter-manager` (PEP 734) solve the `stress_test` bottleneck?\n    *   *Verdict:* PEP 734 is experimental in 3.13/3.14. `Multiprocessing` is battle-tested.\n\n4.  **Folder Inspection:**\n    *   `Get-ChildItem D:\\Dmarket_bot\\specs`\n    *   `Get-ChildItem D:\\Dmarket_bot\\memory\\checkpoints`\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Audit Table (Summary).\n    *   Code Snippets (Proof).\n    *   GIL Strategy Verdict.\n    *   Ready Signal."}],"timestamp":1771165536061}}
{"type":"message","id":"c3e05351","parentId":"6ace9c6d","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:25:41.913Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing Skill Sets**\n\nI'm currently reviewing the knowledge base file, meticulously cataloging the skills associated with the bot ecosystem. My focus is on extracting and organizing the core functionalities, particularly those related to the Dmarket bot's Python implementation. This initial audit will form the foundation for a thorough \"proof of life\" assessment.\n\n\n**Cataloging Capabilities Deeply**\n\nI've initiated the skill audit, starting with `docs_archive/KNOWLEDGE_BASE.md`, and `openclaw.json`. My analysis is concentrating on the intersection of bot functionalities and Python scripting, especially how the core skills translate into bot operations, like the Dmarket bot. I'm taking notes on skills to prepare for the \"proof of life\" assessment.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771165540964_259","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs_archive/KNOWLEDGE_BASE.md"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771165541092_260","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"openclaw.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771165541199_261","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem skills"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771165541359_262","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/dmarket/api/client.py","limit":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771165541489_263","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Pattern \"import\" -Path \"src/dmarket/api/client.py\" | Select-Object -First 5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771165541551_264","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"tests/integration_sandbox.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771165541659_265","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem src/*.pid"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771165541774_266","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem D:\\Dmarket_bot\\specs"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771165541906_267","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem D:\\Dmarket_bot\\memory\\checkpoints"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5222,"output":253,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5475,"cost":{"input":0.010444,"output":0.003036,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01348}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771165536064}}
{"type":"message","id":"a512cdbc","parentId":"c3e05351","timestamp":"2026-02-15T14:25:41.937Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771165540964_259","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# KNOWLEDGE BASE: FUTURE CAPABILITIES\n\n## ClawHub Skills (20)\n\n1.  **ClawHub-Core**: Central authentication and package management for ClawHub.\n2.  **ClawHub-Deploy**: Automated deployment pipelines for agent skills.\n3.  **ClawHub-Monitor**: Real-time health metrics for distributed agents.\n4.  **ClawHub-Analytics**: Data aggregation and visualization of fleet performance.\n5.  **ClawHub-Secure**: Enhanced security auditing and encryption layers.\n6.  **ClawHub-Market**: Interface for trading computational resources.\n7.  **ClawHub-Connect**: Peer-to-peer networking protocol for agent swarms.\n8.  **ClawHub-Storage**: Decentralized storage integration (IPFS/Arweave).\n9.  **ClawHub-Compute**: Offloading heavy computation to grid nodes.\n10. **ClawHub-Vision**: Advanced computer vision processing pipeline.\n11. **ClawHub-Audio**: High-fidelity audio analysis and synthesis.\n12. **ClawHub-Language**: Specialized NLP models for technical domains.\n13. **ClawHub-Control**: Robotics and hardware interface standard.\n14. **ClawHub-Sim**: Sandbox environment for testing agent behaviors.\n15. **ClawHub-Learn**: Reinforcement learning framework for adaptive agents.\n16. **ClawHub-Search**: Semantic search engine for the ClawHub ecosystem.\n17. **ClawHub-Notify**: Multi-channel notification dispatch system.\n18. **ClawHub-Schedule**: Complex task scheduling and orchestration.\n19. **ClawHub-API**: Universal API gateway for external integrations.\n20. **ClawHub-Identity**: Self-sovereign identity management for agents.\n\n## SkillsMP Skills (20)\n\n1.  **SkillsMP-Finance**: Automated trading and portfolio management strategies.\n2.  **SkillsMP-Social**: Social media trend analysis and engagement automation.\n3.  **SkillsMP-Content**: Generative content creation for various media formats.\n4.  **SkillsMP-Research**: Academic and web research summarization tools.\n5.  **SkillsMP-Code**: Advanced code generation and refactoring assistants.\n6.  **SkillsMP-Design**: Graphic design and UI/UX prototyping automation.\n7.  **SkillsMP-Video**: Video editing and post-production workflows.\n8.  **SkillsMP-Game**: Game asset generation and logic scripting.\n9.  **SkillsMP-Data**: Data cleaning, transformation, and ETL pipelines.\n10. **SkillsMP-Legal**: Contract analysis and legal document drafting.\n11. **SkillsMP-Health**: Health data tracking and personalized wellness advice.\n12. **SkillsMP-Travel**: Travel planning and itinerary optimization.\n13. **SkillsMP-Shop**: E-commerce price tracking and purchasing agents.\n14. **SkillsMP-Edu**: Personalized tutoring and curriculum generation.\n15. **SkillsMP-Support**: Automated customer support and ticketing.\n16. **SkillsMP-Sales**: Lead generation and outreach automation.\n17. **SkillsMP-HR**: Recruitment screening and interview scheduling.\n18. **SkillsMP-Ops**: DevOps and infrastructure management automations.\n19. **SkillsMP-SecOps**: Security operations and threat detection.\n20. **SkillsMP-Admin**: Executive assistant tasks (email, calendar, meetings).\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771165541935}}
